author: Inside Edition
description: Sydney Sweeney and Amanda Seyfried appeared on "Family Feud" along with castmates from their upcoming movie "Housemaid." They showed off their competitive sides as they went up against cast members from Real Housewives All-Stars. Meanwhile, it seems like Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce have chosen a wedding date and venue. The wedding will be on June 13, 2026 at the storied "Ocean House" resort in Watch Hill, Rhode Island.
title: Sydney Sweeney And 'Housemaid' Cast Appear on 'Family Feud'

author: Inside Edition
description: Hotel surveillance footage shows "American Pie" star Tara Reid incoherent and slumping in a wheelchair before being taken to a hospital. In an Inside Edition exclusive, a man who Reid was with that night, Sean Pettiford, is speaking out. Reid told police that when she stepped away from the bar, someone drugged her drink. Pettiford says he did not spike her drink and police say surveillance video does not show "anyone tampering with or adding something to her drink.
title: Man Who Tara Reid Was With At Hotel Bar Speaks Out

author: Inside Edition
description: Texas A&M sophomore Brianna Aguilera was found dead after falling 17 stories from an apartment balcony. Her grieving mother believes there was foul play. Authorities said Thursday, Aguilera "had made suicidal comments previously to friends" and her phone shows "a deleted digital suicide note." Authorities say an intoxicated Aguilera went to her friend's 17th floor apartment where she called her boyfriend, and they argued. Minutes later, a female body lying sprawled on the ground was reported.
title: Texas Death Student Brianna Aguilera's Death Ruled Suicide

author: Inside Edition
description: More than 80% of American households use artificial Christmas trees. At House of Holidays in Queens, New York, they sell both real and fake Christmas trees. For some folks, the real deal is the only way to go. At Anne Ellen Tree Farms in Manalapan, New Jersey, real Christmas trees are flying off the lot. Fir trees are the most popular. Inside Edition got some tips to help pick the best tree for Christmas this year.
title: Tips on How To Select A Christmas Tree

author: Inside Edition
description: President Donald Trump was the guest of honor at the Kennedy Center Friday where he was presented with a new peace award. On Thursday, Trump joked that he was considering a name change. The new Institute of Peace has been renamed the Donald J. Trump Institute of Peace building. First Lady Melania Trump joined the president at the Kennedy Center Friday. Earlier in the day, she read a Christmas story at the National Children's Hospital.
title: Is President Trump Renaming the Kennedy Center After Himself?

author: Inside Edition
description: The stepmother of the cheerleader found dead on a family cruise is speaking out about what happened on the fateful trip in court. Shauntell Kepner says her 18-year-old stepdaughter, Anna, shared a cabin on the Carnival cruise ship with her brother and her 16-year-old stepbrother, who is under suspicion in her slaying. Kepner says she last saw Anna the night before she was found asphyxiated under her bed. Inside Edition producer Will Evans is at the Florida courthouse.
title: Stepmother Of Anna Kepner Speaks Out About Deadly Trip In Court

author: Inside Edition
description: Neighbors in suburban Woodbridge, Virginia, where pipe bomb suspect Brian Cole Jr lived with his parents tell of a long history of eccentric behavior. A friend says Cole was bullied in high school. There is speculation the 30-year-old suspect is on the autism spectrum. The FBI says data from Cole's phone usage matched the movements of the pipe bomber the night of January 5, 2020. Cole appeared in federal court for the first time Friday.
title: Pipe Bomb Suspect Brian Cole Jr Appears in Federal Court

author: Inside Edition
description: A baby seal was all in for happy hour at a bar in New Zealand. The pup was first seen outside, but when a person tried to grab it with a sweater, it ran right into the bar, shocking everyone inside. The young seal probably didn't have the proper ID to buy a drink, so it ran into the bathroom, where it took refuge until officials came to take it away. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Seal Pup Shows Up To Happy Hour At Bar In New Zealand

author: Inside Edition
description: Brian Cole Jr. has been charged with planting pipe bombs in Washington, D.C. the night before the January 6th riot. Cole is 30 years old and lived in Woodbridge, Virginia, 24 miles from The Capitol.
title: Who Is The Alleged DC Pipe Bomber? #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A woman who made headlines for killing her sister in a livestreamed car crash was reportedly killed in a drive by shooting. Reports from Stockton, California, say Obdulia Sanchez died on December 2. In 2017, then-18-year-old Sanchez was driving drunk with her sister and a friend in the back seat of her car, when she crashed the vehicle. She then continued streaming, even showing her sister's dead body to the audience. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Woman Who Livestreamed Car Accident That Killed Sister Dies In Drive By Shooting

author: Inside Edition
description: Trena Brown of Florida says she posted a video to social media of a meal being delivered to her daughter's house by DoorDash. The video shows the delivery driver drop a box, pick the spilled food up off the ground and put it back in the container. He also tried to stomp out the sauce that stained the porch. Brown says the thought of her family eating the food made her sick to her stomach. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Customer Upset After DoorDash Driver Dropped Food, Put It Back In Container

author: Inside Edition
description: William Fastow took to the stand and admitted he was having an affair with Ana Walshe, whose husband, Brian Walshe, is on trial for her murder.
title: Man Who Had Affair With Ana Walshe Testifies In Murder Trial #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: William Fastow took to the stand and admitted he was having an affair with Ana Walshe, whose husband, Brian, is on trial for her murder. Fastow testified that Ana wanted to tell her husband about the affair. Fastow testified he grew concerned when he wasn't able to contact Ana for days after New Year's Day in 2023. Then he said her husband called him on January 4. Prosecutors say Brian cut up Ana's body. Brian Walshe has pled not guilty and says his wife died from a "sudden unexplained death."
title: Man Who Had Affair With Ana Walshe Testifies In Brian Walshe Murder Trial

author: Inside Edition
description: A man knocked on a front door claiming to be lost and needing to make a phone call. The female homeowner's instincts told her not to let him in. Turned out, the man was an escaped inmate who police say is armed and dangerous. His name is Timothy Shane, and he faced charges of having allegedly kidnapped his girlfriend. Authorities say Shane escaped from a hospital after he faked a suicide attempt. The homeowner tells Inside Edition she reported the man to police and he was later found.
title: Escaped Inmate Knocks On Homeowner's Door Asking to Make Phonecall

author: Inside Edition
description: Eleven family members ended up getting trapped in a stalled elevator. While being rescued, the family squeezed through the narrow shaft one by one. Even grandma got a lift. The family could have stuck it out for quite a while. They had plenty of leftovers on-hand, because it was Thanksgiving weekend. Safety experts say the chance of being trapped in an elevator is roughly one in every 100,000 rides.
title: Family Of 11 Trapped In Stalled Elevator

author: Inside Edition
description: A student at New York University was assaulted on a busy New York street. The attacker hit 20-year-old Amelia Lewis from behind before slamming her to the ground. Lewis recounted the ordeal on TikTok, and it got nationwide attention after conservative podcaster Megyn Kelly posted it. James Rizzo, 45, has been charged with persistent sexual abuse, forcible touching and assault. Lewis appeared on "The Megyn Kelly Show" Wednesday.
title: Attacker Charged In Connection With Assault Of NYU Student

author: Inside Edition
description: Authorities say 18-year-old Sawyer Updike was tortured as his frat brothers extinguished cigarettes on his chest and speared his leg with fish hooks. Updike's parents say continuous abuse drove their son to suicide. The University of Texas at Austin said they do not tolerate hazing by any group or individual affiliated with the school. The national chapter of the Sigma Chi fraternity says its investigation resulted in the closure of the local chapter and expulsion of several members.
title: College Student Dies By Suicide After Hazing 'Torture,' Parents Say

author: Inside Edition
description: Breanne O'Brien ended up in the emergency room after she said she drank from a glass straw. O'Brien tells Inside Edition that her straw had broken. She says she needed a CAT scan of her stomach where doctors saw the chunk of glass from her straw. They performed an endoscopy to retrieve the glass, but it had already moved out of her stomach. The mom of six shared her story and coast to coast people started inspecting their glass straws and with many of them throwing them in the garbage.
title: Glass Straw Sends Woman To Emergency Room, She Says

author: Inside Edition
description: It has been almost a year since historic fires devastated Los Angeles, California. Ted Koerner and his dog, Daisy May, are moving to their new home. Koerner's new home is the very first house to be rebuilt in hard-hit Altadena. He tells Inside Edition's Jim Moret he loves everything about his new home. The location is the same but the neighborhood has changed. The school and other houses that were once nearby are gone.
title: Man Moves Into First Rebuilt House in Altadena After Devastating Fires

author: Inside Edition
description: At the age of 88, Ed Bambas is a cashier at a superstore outside Detroit. Sam Wiedenhoffer is an influencer who helps those in need. Wiedenhoffer found the retired auto worker on the job working the cash register. Wiedenhoffer was so moved by Bambas' story, he set up a GoFundMe to help him retire. In less than two days, it raised $1.3 million. Bambas says he plans on spending time with his family during his retirement.
title: Gofundme Raises $1.3 Million To Help 88-Year-Old Retire

author: Inside Edition
description: Bodycam video shows a little girl's rescue from a house fire in Wisconsin. The Racine County Sheriff's Office says it happened on the afternoon of December 1. Fire crews on the scene reported that two people were believed to be in the house. A deputy could hear a child crying through the smoke and went inside to find her. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 4-Year-Old Girl Saved From House Fire That Claimed Lives Of Mother And Dog

author: Inside Edition
description: A decorated Native American World War II veteran has died. Charles Shay was just 19 years old when he landed on Omaha Beach as an Army medic. He is credited with saving wounded soldiers from drowning, carrying them out of harm's way. His selfless actions earned him a Silver Star. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Charles Shay, Native American WWII D-Day Veteran, Dies At 101
